discussion.title: Interpretation of charts in tensorboard
discussion.body: Hi everyone, I'm sorry if the question sounds stupid but I'd like to know how to interpret some charts in tensorboard. Mainly this one search/data/population/complexities I understand the X axis if sor complexities, but not sure to understand the Y axis and the highlighted white number (64.0 and 5279) Many thanks for your help :)

nodes.body: So this plot is basically 3D. x-axis complexity. y-axis is density. The third axis, z-axis (shown in layers of histograms) is the number of steps.
